<HEAD>Toddler Survives Fall</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DES MOINES, Iowa (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A 2-year-old boy fell off a third-story balcony, then promptly got up and began walking around after he landed in the grass with only minor injuries, his mother said. `` Owie, Mommy, owie,'' <PERSON> Julie </PERSON> <PERSON> Brown </PERSON> remembered her son, <PERSON> Matthew </PERSON>, saying after falling off the balcony on Wednesday. Ms. <PERSON> Brown </PERSON>, 27, said she had been rushing around Wednesday trying to get her 8-year-old daughter, <PERSON> Nicole </PERSON>, ready for school. When she left the room for a moment, <PERSON> Matthew </PERSON> apparently tumbled off the balcony. `` I do n't know how he landed, but I guess he got up and was walking around the parking lot,'' Ms. <PERSON> Brown </PERSON> said. <PERSON> Matthew </PERSON> was bleeding at the mouth and chin, and he had other scrapes and bruises, but he was listed in good condition at <ORGANIZATION> Iowa </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Methodist </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Medical </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Center </ORGANIZATION>, a spokesman said. `` It's just a miracle,'' said Ms. <PERSON> Brown </PERSON>. `` You ca n't believe how far it looks from the balcony to the ground.''
