conspiracy. Under questioning by <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> investigators, <PERSON> Doar </PERSON> said he had found no evidence of any racial motivation behind <PERSON> Hastings </PERSON>' prosecution or the subsequent inquiry by the judicial panel. If the subcommittee recommends impeachment, and the full <ORGANIZATION> Judiciary </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Committee </ORGANIZATION> concurs, the <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> must vote whether to impeach <PERSON> Hastings </PERSON>. Then the <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION> would conduct a trial. A two-thirds majority vote of the <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION> is required for conviction and removal from office.
