<HEAD>Joyriding Youngster Leaves Neighborhood In Shambles</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SALINA, Kan. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The 9-year-old boy stole the keys to his father's bus and went on a careening joyride through his neighborhood, smashing into cars, a tree and a house as startled residents tried to stop him. The bus finally came to rest in a trailer park. The boy and a 10-year-old friend were treated for minor injuries, but noone else was hurt. `` He took the keys out of his mother's purse and just went for a joyride,'' said <PERSON> Shelley </PERSON> <PERSON> Hanchett </PERSON>, who works with the boy's mother. The boy's father drives a 23-passenger bus used to transport special education students; the bus was severely damaged in the incident Wednesday. `` I heard tires squealing and saw it coming down the street and it sideswiped my car. It then turned the corner ... on two wheels and disappeared. I tried to get the license plate number, but it was going too fast,'' said <PERSON> Reaba </PERSON> <PERSON> Collins </PERSON>. The bus sideswiped two parked cars. It turned north, then east and hit a pickup truck. Then it crossed a street and ripped limbs from a tree in the front yard of a house. `` I saw it hit the tree so I ran out of the house toward the bus to open its door,'' said <PERSON> Joyce </PERSON> <PERSON> Davis </PERSON>, who was visiting in the house. `` It backed up and came toward me, so I ran. It then hit the house. His eyes were wide open. He looked scared.'' <PERSON> Richard </PERSON> <PERSON> Edwards </PERSON> said he ran out of his house after watching the bus hit a street sign. `` I ran out and tried to reach in the window to stop the kid, but he started changing gears and sped off,'' said <PERSON> Edwards </PERSON>, adding that the boy locked the doors when another man tried to reach in the window. <PERSON> Steve </PERSON> <PERSON> Goodwin </PERSON> said he was painting his house when he saw the bus coming down the street. `` The bus finally came to a stop after he hit the last car. He just let go of the steering wheel and stood up,'' <PERSON> Goodwin </PERSON> said. The 10-year-old had been hiding under a seat, <PERSON> Goodwin </PERSON> said. The two boys then wandered around the bus because they could n't get out of the jammed doors, he said. `` The driver kept saying, ` I ca n't let my mom catch me now,'' <PERSON> Goodwin </PERSON> said.
