<TEXT>
 A woman armed with a handgun opened fire at an elementary school in this affluent north <LOCATION> Chicago </LOCATION> suburb today, wounding as many as six people, police said. Patrolman <PERSON> Gary </PERSON> <PERSON> Schultz </PERSON> said the woman, who appeared to be in her 20s, opened fire at <ORGANIZATION> Hubbard </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Woods </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Elementary </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> School </ORGANIZATION> without warning. Spokeswoman <PERSON> Mary </PERSON> <PERSON> Harris </PERSON> at <ORGANIZATION> Evanston </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Hospital </ORGANIZATION> said `` I think we have six'' victims from the shooting. `` They just came in,'' she said, adding she did not yet know the extent of their injuries or how many were children. No further details were available immediately.
