<DATELINE>WINNETKA, Ill. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A woman carrying at least two handguns opened fire in an elementary school Friday, killing one child and critically wounding five others. She then fled to a nearby home and shot a seventh person, police said. `` There was blood all over the classroom and desks knocked over'' as the children panicked and attempted to flee or hid under desks, said <LOCATION> Glencoe </LOCATION> Patrolman <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Ceglieski </PERSON>. Police believe the woman had set fire earlier in the day to another home eight blocks away where she worked as a housekeeper in this affluent <LOCATION> North </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Shore </LOCATION> suburb of <LOCATION> Chicago </LOCATION>, according to Sgt. <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> Geier </PERSON> of the <LOCATION> Wilmette </LOCATION> police. He was assisting in the arson investigation. <PERSON> Joe </PERSON> <PERSON> Sumner </PERSON>, director of operations for <LOCATION> Winnetka </LOCATION> police, identified the woman as <PERSON> Lori </PERSON> <PERSON> Dann </PERSON>, 30. The <ORGANIZATION> FBI </ORGANIZATION> said it had `` an investigative interest'' in her and <PERSON> Madison </PERSON>, <LOCATION> Wis. </LOCATION>, Police Lt. <PERSON> William </PERSON> <PERSON> Sprague </PERSON> said she had been arrested there March 14 on a charge of retail theft. He gave no further details. More than five hours after the initial shooting, the woman remained barricaded inside the home along a tree-lined neighborhood. Heavily armed police encircled the dwelling and a hostage-negotiating team was on the scene, but had not established contact with the woman. `` It's extremely scary. She's just an ordinary citizen and she went through and set all this up. She is n't exactly stable,'' said <ORGANIZATION> Northbrook </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Police </ORGANIZATION> Commander <PERSON> Randy </PERSON> <PERSON> Walters </PERSON>, who was assisting local police at the barricade site. `` The idea is to go in and take custody, not 