s that you always get the small fry. This time we got one of the big guys.'' <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> Attorney <PERSON> Robert </PERSON> <PERSON> Merkle </PERSON>, who prosecuted <PERSON> Lehder </PERSON> in <LOCATION> Jacksonville </LOCATION>, said the conviction is a psychological boost to all agencies fighting drug trafficking. `` Every war in history has seen battles which have practical consequences byeond the immediate consequence of the battlefied,'' he said. `` By that, I mean that they serve to catalyze national will to win the war, or serve as a pyschological defeat for the other side.'' In that sense, <PERSON> Lehder </PERSON>'s conviction was `` a very real, tangible victory for the <LOCATION> American </LOCATION> people and for <LOCATION> Colombia </LOCATION>,'' <PERSON> Merkle </PERSON> said.
