</ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Guard </ORGANIZATION> officers on exemptions in the zero tolerance policy. But <PERSON> Trainor </PERSON> said the changes do n't mean the <ORGANIZATION> Coast </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Guard </ORGANIZATION> is abandoning enforcement of the policy. `` We are part of the national effort to stamp out drugs in this country,'' <PERSON> Trainor </PERSON> said. `` We're holding everybody accountable for his own actions.'' The <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Civil </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Liberties </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Union </ORGANIZATION> is conducting a review of its own, said attorney <PERSON> Barbara </PERSON> <PERSON> Levinson </PERSON>. `` From reports I've heard, <ORGANIZATION> Coast </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Guard </ORGANIZATION> officers are jumping on board and not bothering to check safety _ they're going right to a search. That means people's billfolds, that means drawers, that means closets,'' she said. `` The search of every nook and cranny when there's no reasonable cause _ that violates people's constitutional rights.
