<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The voice of <PERSON> Yogi </PERSON> <PERSON> Bear </PERSON>, <PERSON> Huckleberry </PERSON> <PERSON> Hound </PERSON>, Quick Draw <PERSON> McGraw </PERSON> and dozens of other cartoon characters loved by a generation of Americans has fallen silent. <PERSON> Charles </PERSON> <PERSON> Dawson </PERSON> <PERSON> Butler </PERSON> is dead at age 71. <PERSON> Daws </PERSON> <PERSON> Butler </PERSON>, as he was professionally known at Hanna-Barbera Productions, died of a heart attack Wednesday at <ORGANIZATION> Cedars-Sinai </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Medical </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Center </ORGANIZATION>, the studio announced Thursday. <PERSON> Butler </PERSON> had suffered a stroke and had been battling pneumonia in the past few months, the studio said. `` I just do n't know how the industry will get along without him. There are a lot of people who can imitate <PERSON> Daws </PERSON> but he was the original,'' said <PERSON> Janet </PERSON> <PERSON> Waldo </PERSON>, who was the voice of <PERSON> Judy </PERSON> <PERSON> Jetson </PERSON> on `` The Jetsons'' series.
