<HEAD>Bond Prices Slip</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Bond prices slipped in light dealings this morning as inflation worries continued to weigh on the market despite a new government report that consumer prices rose only modestly in April. The <ORGANIZATION> Treasury </ORGANIZATION>'s bellwether 30-year bond edged down -LRB- point, or about $ 1.25 for every $ 1,000 in face value, by midday as its yield rose to 9.29 percent from 9.27 percent late Thursday. As trading got underway today, the government said consumer prices rose 0.4 percent in April, compared with a 0.5 percent rise in March. While low inflation is usually seen as good news for bond investors, the report failed to inspire any buying in today's market That was partly because the size of the increase had been widely expected, and partly because investors remain fearful that the economy is growing so quickly that inflation may eventually accelerate, analysts said. <PERSON> William </PERSON> <PERSON> V. </PERSON> <PERSON> Sullivan </PERSON> <PERSON> Jr. </PERSON>, director of money market research at <ORGANIZATION> Dean </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Witter </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Reynolds </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, said the reaction `` is the hallmark of a bear market.'' `` There is some good news in the April statistics that should allay concerns that inflation is accelerating, and the market ignores that. It gravitates to bad news,'' he said. In the secondary market for <ORGANIZATION> Treasury </ORGANIZATION> bonds, prices of short-term governments slipped 1-32 point, intermediate maturities fell 3-32 point and 20-year issues were off 9-32 point, according to <ORGANIZATION> Telerate </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, a financial information service. The movement of a point is equivalent to a change of $ 10 in the price of a bond with a $ 1,000 face value. The <ORGANIZATION> Merrill </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Lynch </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Daily </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Treasury </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Index </ORGANIZATION>, which measures price movements on all outstanding <ORGANIZATION> Treasury </ORGANIZATION> issues with maturities of a year or longer, was off 0.07 at 108.68. The <ORGANIZATION> Shearson </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Lehman </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Hutton </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Daily </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Treasury </ORGANIZATION> Bond Index, which makes a similar measurement, fell 0.95 to 1,137.11. <ORGANIZATION> Moody </ORGANIZATION>'s Investment Grade Corporate Bond Index, which measures price movements on 80 corporate bonds with maturities of five years or longer, was up 0.02 at 274.66. Yields on three-month <ORGANIZATION> Treasury </ORGANIZATION> bills rose 10 basis points to 6.24 percent. A basis point is one-hundredth of a percentage point. Six-month bills rose 5 basis points to 6.60 percent and one-year bills rose 4 basis points at 6.95 percent. The federal funds rate, the interest on overnight loans between banks, traded at 7 -LRB- percent, up from 6 15-16 percent late Thursday.
